<br>
As a 59 troubadour, I would say ...  you should NOT be requesting specific songs from a bard.  Any high level bard that doesn't know they're songs well enough to improvise on the spot based on the composition of the group, the various types of mobs, and the speed of the kills isn't worth having in your group. <br>
<br>
Bottom line, if you think the bard is so poor that you have to recommend songs, then kick them out of the group.  <br>
<br>
I suppose, this question is akin to the mage asking the warrior to switch out his 2 weapons for a 2hs, bash more, and always taunt every 6 seconds....<br>
<br>
Wyndaria, <br>
59 Troubadour, Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
PS - Please excuse the boldness of this next statement.  Bards are one of the most complicated classes in EQ.  They have a diverse line up of songs and must change their line up frequently based on each situation and group compostion.  Bards can effectively do any of these:  slow, haste, more haste, resists, ds, more ds, heals, mana, utility, snare, mez, charm, and dots.  <br>
<br>
Bard topics are covered well at: <br>
